HEADWORD: Lunated
<hw>Lu"na*ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>lunatus</ets> crescent-shaped, p. p.
of <ets>lunare</ets> to bend like a crescent, fr. <ets>luna</ets> the
moon.]</ety> <def>Crescent-shaped; resembling the crescent moon; <as>as,
a <ex>lunate</ex> leaf; a <ex>lunate</ex> beak; a <ex>lunated</ex>
cross.</as></def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lunular, bicephalous, crescent(prenominal),
crescent-shaped.</syn>⟦br⟧
